From 1023b5154958ddf7d3b8320fddb4030551c7013d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 16:57:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 47/48] Add warpkeep durable terminal sessions (oh-my-warp)

A transparent, dtach-style session keeper bundled into the warp-oss binary
(hidden warpkeep/warpkeep-master worker subcommands, like the terminal server).
The shell runs in a detached master that owns an inner PTY and survives the GUI
dying; an attach client relays bytes verbatim so Warp keeps rendering blocks/AI.
On reattach the master replays a ring buffer so the screen repaints. Orphaned
sessions auto-recover after a crash; a flock-based single-attach lock prevents
mirroring.

Sockets/PTY fds are kept BLOCKING with reads gated by poll: a non-blocking
write_all of a large burst (Warp's multi-KB shell-bootstrap init script) would
hit WouldBlock and silently drop bytes, breaking the bootstrap. On BSD/macOS the
accepted stream inherits the listener's non-blocking flag, so it is reset to
blocking.
